09/04/2004
SOFIA, Bulgaria -- The Agency for Child Protection (ACP), in co-operation with the interior ministry and the Agency for Social Assistance, has drafted a plan aimed at reducing the number of child beggars, according to ACP head Shirin Mestan.
In an interview with the Sofia daily <I>24 Chasa</I>, Mestan said the plan is directed at towns with the largest number of young beggars, predominantly of Roma origin.
She said the plan includes legal measures against parents who force their children to beg, including stripping the adults of parental rights in more serious cases.
(24 Chasa - 09/04/04)
